<div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" it=
emtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">What is M=
eant by Greatest Common Factor (GCF)?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"s=
uggestedAnswer acceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https=
://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>The greatest number among a=
ll the <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers/common-factors/">common f=
actors</a> of two or more numbers is called the greatest common factor or G=
CF. For any two <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers/">numbers</a>, t=
he GCF is the largest number that divides the two given numbers. GCF can be=
 calculated by using the basic <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers/a=
rithmetic-operations/">arithmetic operations</a> in mathematics i.e. divisi=
on, multiplication, and prime factorization.</p></div></div></div><div item=
scope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D=
"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">How to Find the Gr=
eatest Common Factor (GCF)?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAn=
swer acceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.=
org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>To find the greatest common factor of=
 two or more <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers/natural-numbers/">n=
atural numbers</a>, there are 3 methods that can be used - listing out of t=
he common factors, prime factorization, and <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.=
com/numbers/division/">division</a> method. Each method requires division a=
nd multiplication to obtain the GCF. For example, the <a href=3D"https://ww=
w.cuemath.com/numbers/gcf-of-14-and-35/">GCF of 14 and 35</a> is 7. By usin=
g the listing common factors method, the <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com=
/numbers/factors-of-14/">factors of 14</a> are 1, 2, 7, 14 and the <a href=
=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers/factors-of-35/">factors of 35</a> are 1=
, 5, 7, 35. The two common factors are 1 and 7 out of which 7 is the larges=
t. Therefore, 7 is the GCF of 14 and 35.</p></div></div></div><div itemscop=
e=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"htt=
ps://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">What is the Greatest C=
ommon Factor of Two Prime Numbers?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"sugg=
estedAnswer acceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://=
schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>A prime number has only two fa=
ctors (1 and itself). Hence, two <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers=
/prime-numbers/">prime numbers</a> cannot have any common factor other than=
 1. Therefore, the greatest common factor of two prime numbers is always 1.=
 For example, the <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers/gcf-of-5-and-7=
/">greatest common factor of 5 and 7</a> is 1.</p></div></div></div><div it=
emscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">What is the Gre=
atest Common Factor of 24 and 54?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"sugge=
stedAnswer acceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://s=
chema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>The <a href=3D"https://www.cuem=
ath.com/numbers/factors-of-24/">factors of 24</a> are 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 12,=
 and 24. The <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers/factors-of-54/">fac=
tors of 54</a> are 1, 2, 3, 6, 9, 18, 27, and 54. The common factors of 24 =
and 54 are 1, 2, 3, and 6. Hence, the <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/nu=
mbers/gcf-of-24-and-54/">GCF of 24 and 54</a> is 6.</p></div></div></div><d=
iv itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" item=
type=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">What is the=
 GCF of 15 and 20?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer acce=
ptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answe=
r"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>The <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers=
/factors-of-15/">factors of 15</a> are 1, 3, 5, and 15. The <a href=3D"http=
s://www.cuemath.com/numbers/factors-of-20/">factors of 20</a> are 1, 2, 4, =
5, 10, and 20. The common factors of 15 and 20 are 1 and 5. Thus, the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers/gcf-of-15-and-20/">GCF of 15 and 20</=
a> is 5.</p></div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-questi=
on" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 it=
emprop=3D"name text">How to Find GCF and LCM?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemp=
rop=3D"suggestedAnswer acceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>GCF (greatest comm=
on factor) and LCM (least common multiple) can be found by any of the metho=
ds written below:</p><ul>
<li>Listing method</li>
<li>Prime factorization method</li>
<li>Division method</li>
</ul><p>All the methods are used differently for GCF ad LCM.</p></div></div=
></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEnt=
ity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">Ar=
e GCF and HCF the Same?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer=
 acceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/=
Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>The greatest common factor is abbreviated=
 as GCF and is also known as the <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/numbers=
/hcf-highest-common-factor/">Highest Common Factor</a> (HCF). So, yes, GCF =
and HCF are the same.</p></div></div></div><div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"col=
lapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Que=
stion"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">Is GCF Greater Than LCM?</h3><div itemsco=
pe=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer acceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answ=
er" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>The LC=
M is the least common multiple of the given numbers that can be divided by =
both the numbers, while the GCF is the greatest common factor of the given =
numbers that divide both the numbers. Thus, for any two numbers, the LCM of=
 the numbers is greater than the GCF of the numbers.</p></div></div></div><=
div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" ite=
mtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">How to Fin=
d the Greatest Common Factor of a Polynomial?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemp=
rop=3D"suggestedAnswer acceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=
=3D"https://schema.org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>The greatest commo=
n factor of a <a href=3D"https://www.cuemath.com/algebra/polynomials/">poly=
nomial</a> can be found by following the steps listed below:</p><ul>
<li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Observe all the terms of the given polynomial =
carefully.</li>
<li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Find the numbers or variables that are common =
in all the terms.</li>
</ul><p>That will be the required GCF of polynomial.</p></div></div></div><=
div itemscope=3D"" class=3D"collapsed-question" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" ite=
mtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question"><h3 itemprop=3D"name text">How do you=
 Factor Out the GCF?</h3><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"suggestedAnswer ac=
ceptedAnswer" class=3D"collapsed-answer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Ans=
wer"><div itemprop=3D"text"><p>GCF of two or more numbers can be obtained b=
y using the prime factorization method that is done only in a few steps. Th=
ey are:</p><ul>
<li>List out the prime factors of all the numbers.</li>
<li>Circle the common prime factors among all the numbers.</li>
<li>Multiply all the circled numbers to find the GCF.</li>
</ul></div></div></div></div>
